Baroka Football Club recently appointed former Black Leopards Football Club Coach, Dylan Kerr on a three year deal.
Kerr succeeds Zambian international Wedson Nyirenda who vacated his position after a series of poor results.
The Malta born football mentor previously coached United States football club Phoenix. He also worked as football development officer in Scotland. He worked extensively for the Football Association of England and qualified for various Union of European Football Associations badges.
Story: Herbert Rachuene
